Hope you are well! 
I must say that I am healthy as can be! 
Love, Sig. 
July 24th '32, 
North Platte Neb. 
12:45 P.M. 
Sunday! 
My sweet girl,
When we arrived in Alliance the mail was all in favor of me - & from my dear girl! I was so happy & felt so fine after that letter! 
I am more & more convinced of what a fine girl you are, sweetheart! 
Looking forward to being with you again is a great great pleasure, & is also the source of my happiness! I am anxious to tell you of all the experiences & happenings on this trip! At present I am in a lovely little tourist cabin-just thru with a bachelor meal & must clean up dishes etc. 
Nothing to do all afternoon, so I can take my time to this letter! 
In the morning I am ex-pecting to receive letters 

of introduction to influence men in this city from Dad's friends in Omaha! Hope they have "cooked up" something that will in the near future be of value to getting me back into aviation, & in this beautiful North Platte Valley country!
Can't tell - it may be the beginning of something! By the way - I played beautifully at Chadron Normal school & on a 10'-Steinway concert grand! No radio broadcasts are possible, as Kearney neb. is our last stunt - & already arranged! I have been thinking of you all of the time - you dear girl! Certainly you are the sweetest person to think about! To be with you is the best tho'! 
JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER

