It won't be long 'til we will again be together! I've had some terrible spells of sadness over it all, but I feel much better when I think of how true & honest you are with me! 
I know that the love we have for eachother makes it a sure thing, & that distance doesn't have any effect on us as far as forgetting eachother is concerned! We can't do that sweetheart, becuase our tho'ts are the same! I was just wondering last nite what you would think if you knew "we" were lost in the sand hills,- roads goin' every direction & of course we didn't follow the right one! Several times at nite while driving along & looking

at the big dipper (& the moon) I would wonder as to whether or not my sweetheart should just happen to be looking at it too! 
Ha! Couldn't see 'ya anyway if you were lookin' at the moon, could I? I bet-U-not! The reason I ahve been gasing at the sky instead of the surrounding country is because I knew that if you were outside-it woudl be the only place we could both look & be seeing the "same" things! Well so much for that! Yee! I've a bright chile, eh? 
I believe we'll arrive in Branson Thurs. evening! I love you, you blessed girl, & never in the world could I do anything but care more & more for you!! You know it's true sweetheart! 
Always I love you,
Your Sig. 
P.S. Glad you have enjoyed the conference! 
I'll be seein' you by Friday I think son. 
JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER 

